outputs.output_descr:
The aim of the project is to effectively facilitate and coordinate the UN activities in Zambia. The following core results are expected from the UN in Zambia Delivering as One: 
(i)	Visible One UN voice and advocacy on human rights, MDGs and human development;
(ii)	Consistent One UN policy analysis, expression and guidance;
(iii)	A strategic set of UN Joint Programmes in value add areas of the UN's work in Zambia;
(iv)	Enhanced UN aid coordination, predictability and transparency;
(v)	A common approach to strengthening national institutions and systems, optimizing the UN contribution to national capacity development, and 
(vi)	Business efficiencies and savings from common operations and joint learning to minimize duplication and transaction costs. 

The overall outcome at the end of the project will be a better coordinated, effective and efficient UN system that delivers results in Zambia, to support a sub set of national development priorities as articulated in the SNDP. This sub-set defines those areas where the UN brings a specific UN value-add.
